Pour the mixture into the tin and bake for 50 mins - 1 hr until the cake feels firm and a little crusty on top. Cool in the tin then wrap in more parchment and foil and keep for 3-5 days before eating if you can – it’ll become softer and stickier the longer you leave it, up to 2 weeks.

', '200g Butter, 1 large Egg, 4 tbs Milk, 200g Golden Syrup, 85g Black Treacle, 85g Brown Sugar, 100g Oatmeal, 250g Self-raising Flour, 1 tbs Ground Ginger', 'Caramel', '52902.jpg');
INSERT IGNORE INTO dishes (idMeal, name, category, area, instructions, ingredients, tags, thumb_file) VALUES ('52813', 'Kentucky Fried Chicken', 'Chicken', 'American', 'Preheat fryer to 350°F. Thoroughly mix together all the spice mix ingredients.

